                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/82.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-05T10:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 4, 9 p.m. Can the Department fully confirm the entire
                    information given in this telegram? It is stated here that Chao himself was
                    executed prior to June 27, 7 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
